Monthly SAG Regional P&L Report
Standard Operating Procedure (SOP)

Step 1 - Get the Case List from Nalini
•	Before the flash deadline, email Nalini (the business person in charge) to request:
•	The fee/income cases for the month
•	The case list with customer names and effort splits by team
Note: Nalini usually only has final numbers towards month end, so early confirmation may not be possible.
•	The case list will indicate which team's effort drove each fee:
•	Singapore
•	Hong Kong
•	Indonesia (Indo team)

Step 2 - Refresh the SAG Tabs
•	Open the SAG report file saved in the PF folder.
•	Refresh all tabs in the workbook - this is mostly automated.
•	For Hong Kong, note the following:
•	Head count remains in Hong Kong
•	Direct costs are offshored/booked in Singapore
•	Net allocation flows back to Hong Kong
•	There are two SAG teams in HK, so there will be one HK P&L sheet per team

Step 3 - Extract EPM Data
•	Log into EPM and extract data for the SAG / M&A product (previously called "M&A", now referred to as "SAG M&A").
•	Extract all countries (regional scope).
•	Filter to show income only.
•	Key things to watch for:
•	If income was accrued in a prior month under a blank/uninvoiced entry, it will reverse out in the current month when the invoice is raised - net effect is zero. This confirms the number already flowed through last month.
•	If a large accrual appears and management wants to recognise it in the accrual month, a manual EPM reversal is needed to prevent double-counting when the actual invoice comes in.

Step 4 - Update the Case List with Effort Splits
•	Open the case list file (found in the SH folder).
•	For each case/fee received from Nalini, indicate which team's effort it belongs to (Singapore, Hong Kong, or Indonesia).
•	The sum of all effort splits must tie to the total income figure in the P&L.
•	Every month, shift the monthly columns (drop the oldest month, add the new current month) to maintain a rolling year-to-date view for year-on-year comparison.
Note: Last year's case list numbers may differ slightly from current figures due to exchange rate rebasing - this is normal.

Step 5 - Update the Regional P&L - Manual Split
•	In the Regional P&L tab, manually split the total income into the three teams: Singapore, Hong Kong, and Indonesia.
•	Use the effort splits from the case list (Step 4) to populate this.
•	The total of the three splits must tie to the overall income total.
•	Also bring in prior year comparatives (e.g. November and December of last year) and shift them month by month as the year progresses.

Step 6 - Accrue the Indonesia Cost (Monthly)
•	Every month, post a cost accrual in PSGL for Indonesia because:
•	Indonesia helps with some of the work and bills quarterly
•	Since payment is only quarterly, the cost must be accrued monthly
•	Who provides the cost figure: 
Claudia (from the Indonesia side) will send the expense amount, usually before the 31st of the month.
•	Where to post: 
PSGL, as a cost accrual (direct billing cost).
•	Deadline: 
Post within the month (by month end / within the PSGL BD+2 deadline at the latest).
•	When Indonesia eventually sends the quarterly bill, the accruals reverse and the actual payment is recorded.

Step 7 - Final Checks and Send-Out
•	Confirm the case list is attached and updated.
•	Verify all tab refreshes are complete and numbers are consistent.
•	Send the completed report to Wei Sing (overall overseer).
Note: The MD ("Way") is the person in charge of the team, but Wei Sing oversees at a higher level, similar to how Gunnish oversees PF.
•	CC the relevant parties as per the usual distribution list - request to be included in the email thread.


